 White trees, ice-blue lighting and white draping set the mood for Pulse Dance Studio’s annual winter ball. This year the studio decided that it wanted to give back to the community, and the proceeds of the evening were donated to CANSA. ALSO READ: Madelein Rust gesels oor Kanker Schmanker, Doodsengel Even though it was a cool winter’s evening, the entertainment was hot. Several dancers from the studio showcased their talents with ballroom and modern dances as well as a good old-fashioned sokkie. During the evening, several singers also took to the stage to entertain guests. 